sourcesContent: import { Fragment, useEffect } from 'react' import { Row, Col, CardText } from 'reactstrap' import Prism from 'prismjs' import BreadCrumbs from '@Components/breadcrumbs' import Card from '@Components/card-snippet' import NavBasic from './NavBasic' import NavBorder from './NavBorder' import NavCenter from './NavCenter' import NavEnd from './NavEnd' import NavVertical from './NavVertical' import NavVerticalBorder from './NavVerticalBorder' import NavSquareBorder from './NavSquareBorder' import NavDivider from './NavDivider' import { navBasic, navBorder, navCenter, navDivider, navEnd, navSquareBorder, navVertical, navVerticalBorder } from './NavComponentSourceCode' const NavComponent = () => { useEffect(() => { Prism.highlightAll() }, []) return ( The base nav component provides a strong foundation for building all types of navigation components. Use Class .wrap-border with your nav tag to wrap your nav with a border Use Class .justify-content-center with your nav tag to align your nav to center. Use Class .justify-content-end with your nav tag to align your nav to End. Use prop vertical with nav tag to make it vertical. To wrap with border, use .wrap-border class. To wrap with square border, use .square-border class with .wrap-border class. To add divider, use .dropdown-divider class to NavItem ) } export default NavComponent
